# Reusable Components First

When building or modifying UI, always extract shared patterns into standalone components before duplicating markup.

## Rules

- **Before writing inline UI**, check if a similar pattern already exists elsewhere in the codebase. If it does, extract it into a shared component and reuse it.
- **Never duplicate UI blocks** across files. If the same markup appears (or would appear) in two or more places, create a component immediately.
- **Self-contained components**: Each reusable component should own its own hooks, state, and conditional rendering logic (e.g. an install banner that internally calls `usePwaInstall()` and returns `null` when not needed).
- **Colocation**: Place player-facing shared components in `src/app/(player)/player/` alongside their consumers. Place app-wide shared components in `src/components/`.

## Example

```tsx
// BAD — duplicated install banner in home.tsx and queue-screen.tsx
{showBanner && (
  <div className="...">
    <Download />
    <p>Install CourtFlow</p>
    {/* 20 lines of conditional rendering */}
  </div>
)}

// GOOD — extracted into <InstallCard /> used everywhere
import { InstallCard } from "./install-card";

<InstallCard />
```
